<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-17T15:42:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-17T15:42:00-05:00" n="340" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/564: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Shea</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-17T16:00:00-04:42"><hi rend="italic">March
                                            17</hi> [<hi rend="italic">16?</hi>], <hi rend="italic">1920—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 17—1
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>30. Suppressed excitement here following report of assault on
                                Peruvian Legation and officials in La Paz. It is believed that Peru
                                will mobilize an army, in which event Chile will mobilize also.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Shea</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>